wnstream processing to complete","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"The failure is: handler awaits downstream processing before returning response. This is code-structure verification—can be caught by spying on function calls and verifying res.send is invoked before any downstream processor await. Unit test with mocks catches the wrong await pattern. Downstream delays (behavior 4) are separate.","test_description":"Mock queue and downstream processor. Spy on handler calls. Assert: res.status(200).send() is invoked before await on downstream processor. Verify the handler function returns immediately after queuing, not after processing. Test with a slow mock processor to confirm no await ordering.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.65,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Response arrives within 3 seconds wall-clock time even when downstream processing is slow and concurrent","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Timing SLAs cannot be verified with instant mocks—they hide latency. Real or simulated delays are required to prove the handler doesn't block downstream. Concurrent event handling must be tested with multiple in-flight requests and real/simulated processing latency. Need wall-clock measurement, not mock timing.","test_description":"Send multiple concurrent webhook requests (5–10 events). Inject realistic delays into downstream processing (e.g., 1–2 second sleeps per event). Measure HTTP response latencies for each request. Assert: all responses complete within 3 seconds wall-clock time, even when earlier events are still processing. Verify no response is blocked by prior event processing.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"An event whose ID was already received is not written to queue a second time (idempotency)","minimum_level":"Integration","justificatio